Module ProjectEthos

Package ProjectEthos

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccessManagement
    This class will handle the Access Management and essentially act as a controller.
    Alarm
    This class is an alarm object that will be used as part of the schedule management class.
    ApplicationToConnect  
    Door
    This class is an door object that will be used as part of the panel switch class.
    EthosProgram
    The ProjectEthos class will act as a master class.
    EventLog
    This object will contain the Event Log information for all the changes occurring in the system.
    Group
    This class will allow for groups to be created and managed within Ethos
    IDCard
    This class will is representative of a physical ID card.
    PanelSwitch
    The PanelSwitch class will allow for the routing of signals to various Door objects.
    ProximitySensor
    The ProximitySendor class will detail the proximity sensor that is assigned to a Door class
    Report
    The report class will allow for report to be created, generated, and extracted from Ethos.
    RFIDScanner
    The RFIDScanner class will detail the proximity sensor that is assigned to a Door class
    Schedule
    This class will be used as one of many schedule objects for the schedule management for the building access.
    ScheduleManagement
    This class will manage every schedule object which will be used for the building access.
    Site
    This class is a site object, it is representative of a physical location.
    SystemAPIGateWay
    This class is a SystemAPIGateWay object, this will hold all the system so Ethos can interface with other systems.This will contain the name if the application, the server address, the aAdmin account and Admin password for the systems.
    User
    This class will will represent an employee.
